BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART:20200110T220000Z
DTEND:20200111T010000Z
DTSTAMP:20260626T224051Z
UID:17ml76e8aq4jg77rclqv0g5sr9@google.com
CREATED:20191221T203729Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Hi Aaron\,</p><p>Thank you for sending over your availabilit
 y to come onsite to meet with the team! Please see your interview informati
 on below and take a moment to respond to this email to confirm the below da
 y and time work for you.<br><br><strong>DATE &amp\; TIME:&nbsp\;</strong>Fr
 iday\, January 10th\, 2:00pm-5:30pm PST<br><em>Please arrive 5-10 minutes e
 arly for your interviews.<br></em><br><strong>SCHEDULE:</strong><br>2:00pm-
 2:45pm:&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/samar-shah-63861812/">Sa
 mar Shah</a>\, Product Manager &amp\;&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.linkedin.c
 om/in/ebrownrout/">Eric Brownrout</a>\, Product Manager<br>2:45pm-3:15pm:&n
 bsp\;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ebloch/">Ethan Bloch</a>\, CEO<br
 >3:15pm-4:00pm:&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/carolyn-satenber
 g-esq-28b17332/">Carolyn Satenberg</a>\, Head of People &amp\;&nbsp\;<a hre
 f="https://www.linkedin.com/in/nathaniel-escribano-82ab0434/">Nathaniel Esc
 ribano</a>\, Software Engineer<br>4:00pm-4:45pm:&nbsp\;<a href="https://www
 .linkedin.com/in/karthikhariharan">Karthik Hariharan</a>\, VP of Engineerin
 g &amp\;&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/heather-lee-41594571/">
 Heather Lee</a>\, Software Engineer<br>4:45pm-5:15pm:&nbsp\;<a href="https:
 //www.linkedin.com/in/carlosrotger/">Carlos Rotger</a>\, Software Engineer<
 br>5:15pm-5:30pm:&nbsp\;<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/karthikharihar
 an">Karthik Hariharan</a>\, VP of Engineering<em><br></em><br>Our office is
  located at 100 Pine Street on the 20th floor. When you arrive\, please che
 ck in at the front desk and ask for Digit. Security will direct you to the 
 correct elevator. Once you arrive on the 20th floor please sign in using th
 e iPad outside of our door and&nbsp\;<strong>be sure to list me\, Clare Gey
 er\, as your host!</strong>&nbsp\;I will greet you.</p><br><p>Let me know i
 f you have any questions in the meantime\, we look forward to seeing you so
 on!</p><p>Cheers!<br>Clare &amp\; the Digit team</p><p><br></p><p><u>Execut
 ion and Delivery</u>&nbsp\;(with me)<br>Be ready to talk about how you orga
 nize projects\, set the execution rhythm for your team\, and get things don
 e. Be ready with examples of how roadblocks your teams encountered and reso
 lved with your support. Also plan to have examples of how you kept your tea
 m motivated through longer efforts.<br><br><u>Vision\, Strategy\, Leadershi
 p</u>&nbsp\;(with a Product Manager)<br>Be ready to talk about the vision f
 or one of your teams and what their purpose was\, and how it fits into the 
 larger company strategy. Talk about your involvement in building the strate
 gy and roadmap for their work over a given time period (months\, quarters\,
  etc). Also talk about any challenges in getting aligned with other functio
 ns (PM\, Design\, Marketing\, Sales\, etc) and how you helped drive consens
 us.<br><br><u>Exec Values</u>&nbsp\;(Ethan\, our founding CEO)<br>We have a
  few core values at Digit and we're looking for folks who align with our mi
 ssion. Reading up on Digit\, watching a few videos/podcasts of Ethan's inte
 rviews\, etc. would be good prep for this. At our core\, we're looking to m
 ake sure that leaders we bring on are in it for the journey and the Digit's
  mission which is "Effortless Financial Health for Everyone."<br><br><u>Lun
 ch</u>&nbsp\;(with an engineer on the team)<br>We keep this pretty informal
  and call it the "the airport test". If you were stuck in an airport for 5 
 hours with this person\, would you be okay with it? I don't expect you to h
 ave any challenge with this one.<br><br><u>Fearlessness and Truth seeking</
 u>&nbsp\;(Carolyn\, our head of HR\, and one of our other engineers)<br>Be 
 ready to talk through tougher situations that you've encountered as a manag
 er. Conflicts between people on your team\, or people outside your team. Sh
 aring bad news\, helping a direct report through a failure\, sharing critic
 al feedback with your direct reports when they needed to hear it\, handling
  any tougher people issues that you've encountered.<br><br><u>Recap &amp\; 
 Walkout (</u>with me)<br>The last interview with me will just be a recap of
  the day\, and an opportunity for you to ask me any questions. I would love
  to get some feedback from you about our interview process at this point as
  well.<br></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20200106T155016Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Digit Onsite
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
