ORGANIZER;CN=ashleynmahoney@gmail.com:mailto:ashleynmahoney@gmail.com
UID:rda6gv9b38roc27gprics5mbu8@google.com
ATTENDEE;CUTYPE=INDIVIDUAL;ROLE=REQ-PARTICIPANT;PARTSTAT=ACCEPTED;CN=ashley
 nmahoney@gmail.com;X-NUM-GUESTS=0:mailto:ashleynmahoney@gmail.com
ATTENDEE;CUTYPE=INDIVIDUAL;ROLE=REQ-PARTICIPANT;PARTSTAT=ACCEPTED;CN=r.aaro
 n.jones@gmail.com;X-NUM-GUESTS=0:mailto:r.aaron.jones@gmail.com
CREATED:20150317T214556Z
DESCRIPTION:(415) 433-6300\nAn exceptionally stylish supper club\, civilize
 d speakeasy\, a sophisticated saloon. Each of these "personae" is housed in
  a soaring two-story interior distinguished by a gently curving mahogany ba
 r\, fluted columns with ornate capitals\, stunning original art\, plush ban
 quettes\, cozy booths\, starched linens\, glittering glasses\, and polished
  flatware. \nOverall\, the ambiance is pure 1930's and 1940's - tasteful ar
 t moderne reminiscent of the glory days of Cunard and French Line ships. Fa
 shionable and glamorous are the hallmarks. Trendy is simply not a part of t
 he BIX culture. \nThe clientele at BIX ranges from San Francisco movers-and
 -shakers to "savvy travelers" - owner Doug Biederbeck's term for the many d
 iners in the know from out of town who patronize his establishment. \nAll o
 f them step from the featureless alley into another world - a world of supe
 rb cookery and libations\, of sparkling service\, of stylish nostalgia\, of
  polished live jazz. That world is BIX.
LAST-MODIFIED:20221201T150403Z
LOCATION:56 Gold St.\, San Francisco\, CA 94133
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:BIX
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
